The paper deals with the asymptotic expansion of the maximum coding rate of a parallel Gaussian channel with feedback, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The techniques used in the proof involve developing an information spectrum bound, which is a common tool in statistical inference (cs.SI) and signal processing (cs.NI). The paper also mentions the use of the central limit theorem, which is a fundamental concept in probability theory and statistics (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper discusses the water-filling algorithm, which is a well-known optimization technique in machine learning and optimization (cs.LG).
